      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2190: clearBodyOverwrites() clears bodyOverwrite on edition commits but does not clear the mirrored bodyOverwrite copied onto the parent when the latest edition owns the current body. After clearing, clients can still receive the parent with a stale translated current body. When an edited commit is cleared and parent.latestEditionId \u003d\u003d edition id, also erase the parent\u0027s bodyOverwrite before building the signal.\n```suggestion\nif (editIt !\u003d msg-\u003ebody.end() \u0026\u0026 !editIt-\u003esecond.empty()) {\n    toSignal.insert(editIt-\u003esecond);\n    auto parentIt \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(editIt-\u003esecond);\n    if (parentIt !\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end()\n        \u0026\u0026 parentIt-\u003esecond-\u003elatestEditionId \u003d\u003d id) {\n        parentIt-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData.erase(\"bodyOverwrite\");\n    }\n} else {\n    toSignal.insert(id);\n}\n```",
      "revId": "783e26afd63e66eaec62278de36767cb504eeea9",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
