      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 2256: loadMissingBodyOverwrites() is called after SwarmLoaded is emitted, but the new ChatHandler API documents that transforms happen before SwarmLoaded. This means clients first receive unmodified messages, then separate SwarmMessageUpdated signals, causing flicker and making the API contract misleading. Run the overwrite loading before emitting SwarmLoaded, or update the API/comment to describe the two-phase behavior.\n```suggestion\n#ifdef ENABLE_PLUGIN\nif (auto convPtr \u003d convWeak.lock())\n    convPtr-\u003eloadMissingBodyOverwrites();\n#endif\nemitSignal\u003clibjami::ConversationSignal::SwarmLoaded\u003e(id, accountId, conversationId, messages);\n```",
